This article is a presidential proclamation by President Barack Obama to modify the Harmonized Tariff Schedule of the United States (HTS). The proclamation is based on recommendations made by the United States International Trade Commission (USITC) and aims to promote the uniform application of the International Convention on the Harmonized Commodity Description and Coding System and alleviate unnecessary administrative burdens. The modifications include changes to certain footwear and rules of origin under the United States-Chile Free Trade Agreement. The proclamation also reflects modified requirements for a special import quota for upland cotton. The effective dates for the modifications are specified in the proclamation.